title: Area roundup: Palmyra-Macedon girls open with victory
text: Victor 2, Rush-Henrietta 1 (OT) Class D1 quarterfinals Jasper-Troupsburg 3, Naples 0 Tucker Simons, Connor Vangordon, and Deven Brutsman scored for J-T (14-3-1), which advances to the final. Naples finishes with a 12-2-3 record. Boys volleyball Victor 25-23-25-25, Rush-Henrietta 19-25-17-20 Paul Kopp had 13 kills and Brennan Meeks had six kills and 10 digs for Victor (9-7, 5-7). Steven Zarzycki led R-H (7-11, 2-9) with eight digs. Girls swimming Marcus Whitman won the Finger Lakes Invitational for the second straight season, scoring 396 points. The Wildcats finished first in three events, including the 200-yard medley relay with the team of Aislinn Coleman, Courtney Copper, Hailey Rossi and Morgan Smithling in 2:04.74. Copper, who was named Senior of the Meet at Palmyra-Macedon High, won the 200 IM (2:19.65) and Rossi, a freshman, won the 100 breaststroke (1:13.99). Pal-Mac freshman Rachael Mayou won the 200 free (2:07.88) and the 500 free (5:33.59). Team scores: Marcus Whitman 396, Palmyra-Macedon 371, Newark 292, Gananda 288, Midlakes 268, North Rose-Wolcott 262, Geneva 108. Girls volleyball Bloomfield 24-26-25-25, Finney 26-24-19-18 Rebecca Mathis had five aces and six digs, and Shaina Babcock had 4 kills and three blocks for Bloomfield, while Maria Matuck added seven aces, six kills and one block. Wayne 23-25-25-19-25, Honeoye 25-14-23-25-16 Lauren Devaney had 14 kills, 7 aces and 23 digs for the Bulldogs (14-3, 8-2), while Hailey Cornish had 30 assists and Bailey Lis had five blocks. Michele DiNoicola led Wayne (12-4, 10-2) with 22 kills and four aces. Thursday Girls volleyball Eastridge 25-25-19-22-25, Canandaigua 14-18-25-25-23 Rachel Simmons had 15 kills for Canandaigua (6-9) and Harmony Brookins had 17 kills for Eastridge (9-9). By Messenger Post
